Wash and dry all produce. Thinly slice @Persian Cucumber{1}(thinly sliced on a diagonal). Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced). In a #medium bowl{}, combine scallions, cucumber, @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}, @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 1 tsp @Sugar{1%tsp}, and a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%teaspoon}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Halve @Brioche Buns{2}. Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add buns cut sides down and toast until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Set aside.

While buns toast, in a #shallow dish{}, combine @Panko Breadcrumbs{1/2%cup}, 1/2 tsp @Salt{1/2%tsp}, and @Fry Seasoning{2%teaspoon} (save the last teaspoon for step 5). Brush 2 TBSP @Sour Cream{6%tablespoon} (1 packet) onto @Tilapia{11%ounce}, coating all over. Season with salt and pepper. Dip each fillet in panko mixture, coating all over and pressing to adhere.

Heat a ¼-inch layer of @Vegetable Oil{} in pan used for buns over medium-high heat. Add tilapia and cook until panko is golden and fish is cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

In a #small bowl{}, combine remaining sour cream, @Fry Seasoning{1%teaspoon}, and half the @Hot Sauce{2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper.

Cut tilapia into 3-inch pieces. Spread sauce onto cut sides of buns. Fill buns with tilapia and a bit of slaw. Drizzle with remaining hot sauce (to taste). Divide between plates and serve with remaining slaw on the side.

> If there's more fish than will fit, serve it on the side rather than overfilling the sandwich.